# ChatGPT Wiretapper

A lightweight technical SEO diagnostic extension built for Chrome (Manifest V3). It intercepts client-side network response streams on `chatgpt.com` to reveal hidden query intent classifications, autocomplete suggestion layers, and out-of-model search retrieval source attribution in real time.

Written off the back of the foundational technical search pipeline research by **Mark Williams-Cook**.

## 🚀 Key Features

* **Predictive Autocomplete Interception:** Logs exact text suggestion variations offered dynamically as users type.
* **Real-Time Intent Tracking:** Reveals hidden intent classifications (`search`, `shopping`, `text`) which dictate if, how, and where out-of-model data pipelines are routed.
* **Out-of-Model System Breakdown:** Decodes the structural grounding layer chosen to serve answers (`serp`, `labrador`, `bright`), allowing you to accurately map out citation weights and article extraction lengths.
* **Clipboard Compilation:** A one-click copy function outputs neatly formatted diagnostic logs straight into your clipboard for tracking.

## 🛠️ Local Installation (Developer Mode)

1. Clone or download this repository to your local machine.
2. Open Google Chrome and navigate to `chrome://extensions/`.
3. Enable **Developer mode** via the toggle switch in the upper right-hand corner.
4. Click **Load unpacked** in the top-left and select the root directory of this project folder.
5. Open ChatGPT and start running search-intent queries!

## 🔒 Privacy
This utility functions strictly in-memory on the client-side session. It does not collect, store, track, or transmit any user queries, browsing inputs, or extracted metadata URLs to external servers or third parties.